2.) JUBE2 files for mdtest
**************************

   file name              | purpose
   -----------------------+-----------------------------------------------
   mdtest-jube-master.xml | master XML file for the mdtest run in JUBE
   mdtest_specs.xml       | default specifications for the mdtest run
                          | is used by the master XML file
   mdtest.tar.gz          | prepared source files for the mdtest compile step



3.) predefined JUBE2 'tags'
***************************
   JUBE2 tags are used to activate XML statements in the JUBE XML file.
   Here - among other things - it is used to find the right platform files.

   tag list:
     juqueen    -> Jülich HPC system 'JUQUEEN' specific configuration
     juropa2    -> Jülich HPC system 'JUROPA' specific configuration
     juropatest -> Jülich test system 'JUROPATEST' specific configuration
     judge      -> Jülich GPU cluster 'JUDGE' specific configuration
     deep       -> Jülich project cluster 'DEEP' specific configuration
     juniors    -> Jülich project cluster 'JUNIORS' specific configuration



4.) Usage HowTo
***************

  0. prerequisite: JUBE2 installed 
     (assumed, that the CLI is called by 'jube')
     
  1. preparation
     a) platform definition available?
        - predefined platforms are stored in '<JUBE-INST-PATH>/platform/'
	- on 'unknown' systems this definition must be created first
     b) customize mdtest parameters to your demands
     	!!!only the master XML file should be modified!!!
        look in the 'specs' file for the defaults

  2. execute the mdtest/JUBE job
     jube run mdtest-jube-master.xml --tag <platform>

  3. check mdtest/JUBE job state
     jube continue ./benchmark [--id #]

  4. analyse benchmark output  
     jube analyse ./benchmark [--id #]

  5. show results
     jube result ./benchmark [--id #]
